			<span class="by"><span class="byby">by </span><a href="//slashdot.org/~EvilSS">EvilSS</a>  <span class="uid"><a href="//slashdot.org/~EvilSS">( 557649 )</a></span></a></span><span class="writes" style="display:none"> writes:</span> 
			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_64263736"></span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64263736">A stealth layoff is when a firm wants to cut headcount, but doesn't want to announce it to the world. So they make changes to allow them to fire individuals (changing performance standards for example) or to put pressure on individuals to leave voluntarily by changing policies like remote work. Then they can cut that 10% (or whatever) in headcount without tipping off Wall Street and the rest of the world. <br> <br>Just want to point out a simple google search would have given you this information.</div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64263736">

